				<p>This is actually exactly how I make my roasted mushrooms, except I skip the capers and cut down on the butter and oil.  When I make them that way, the mushrooms are still tender and golden but a little less rich, which I prefer.  (I think I may have modeled my recipe on this Gourmet one, in fact.)  BTW, I am totally with you on the steakhouse thing.  If you&#8217;re ever in the Atlanta area, you need to go to Bone&#8217;s which has my favorite steakhouse mushrooms ever, with garlic, butter, and white wine, and a corn souffle that rocked my world.</p>
